&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Req ID&lt;/strong&gt;: FEQ427R279&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Tokyo, Japan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Databricks, our core values are at the heart of everything we do; a culture of proactiveness and customer‑centricity guides us to build a unified platform that makes data and AI accessible to everyone. In &lt;strong&gt;Japan Public Sector&lt;/strong&gt;, we help central ministries, agencies, local governments, and public institutions use data and AI to deliver better, more trusted services to citizens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the senior technical leader for a set of strategic public sector accounts in Japan, using your executive‑level technical credibility and government expertise to shape and execute their data and AI strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting to:&lt;/strong&gt; Director, Field Engineering, Japan&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The impact you will have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own technical strategy&lt;/strong&gt; for key Japan public sector customers, defining the target architecture and roadmap for their Databricks‑based data and AI platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead solution design&lt;/strong&gt; for priority government use cases (e.g., citizen 360 and eligibility, program analytics, smart infrastructure, cybersecurity, fraud/waste/abuse).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design for security and compliance&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring architectures meet public sector expectations on data residency, access control, governance, and auditability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turn pilots into platforms&lt;/strong&gt;, linking Databricks to visible mission outcomes and using those wins to drive expansion across bureaus, departments, and levels of government.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influence the ecosystem&lt;/strong&gt;, collaborating with SIs, cloud providers, and public sector partners to deliver integrated, production‑grade solutions on Databricks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mentor others&lt;/strong&gt;, coaching Solutions Architects and partners on how to work effectively with Japan public sector stakeholders and patterns on the Databricks platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What we look for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10+ years&lt;/strong&gt; in data platforms, analytics, or cloud architecture, including &lt;strong&gt;significant experience with public sector organizations in Japan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to &lt;strong&gt;build trust with senior government stakeholders&lt;/strong&gt; (CIO, CDO, chief architect, bureau/department leaders) and lead high‑stakes technical discussions in Japanese.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical background in &lt;strong&gt;Data Engineering, Data Warehousing/Analytics, AI/ML, or Cloud Architecture&lt;/strong&gt;, with a focus on solution design and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience architecting data and analytics solutions for &lt;strong&gt;public sector use cases&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., citizen services, program analytics, public safety, infrastructure, or cybersecurity).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with &lt;strong&gt;Japan public sector decision‑making and delivery models&lt;/strong&gt;, including how SIs and cloud providers support government projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent &lt;strong&gt;communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;, able to translate mission and policy needs into clear technical approaches and explain them to both technical and non‑technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Language:&lt;/strong&gt; Native‑level Japanese and business‑level English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re excited about helping Japan’s Public Sector use data and AI to deliver better outcomes – while setting the technical bar for our GTM in Japan – we’d love to hear from you.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
